Install GitLab on Ubuntu-14.04
==============================

ServerIP=200.0.0.30

GitLab an open source project which allows users to run a project management system similar to GitHub on their own servers.

Before we install GitLab, may want to configure an SMTP email server so that GitLab can push emails as and when needed. 
They recommend Postfix. So, install Postfix on your server:


$ sudo apt-get install postfix
During installation of Postfix it will ask you some questions; don't skip them. If you did miss it you can always re-configure it using this command:
sudo dpkg-reconfigure postfix
When you run this command choose "Internet Site" and provide the email ID for the domain which will be used by Gitlab.
In my case I provided it with:  user1@mysite.com
Use Tab and create a username for postfix. The Next page will ask you to provide a destination for mail.
In the rest of the steps, use the default options. Once Postfix is installed and configured, let's move on to install GitLab.

Download the packages using wget

$ wget https://downloads-packages.s3.amazonaws.com/ubuntu-14.04/gitlab_7.9.4-omnibus.1-1_amd64.deb
OR
# scp -r ubuntu@192.168.1.222:/home/ubuntu/Desktop/Git/gitlab_7.9.4-omnibus.1-1_amd64.deb .

$ sudo dpkg -i gitlab_7.9.4-omnibus.1-1_amd64.deb

Now it's time to configure and start GitLabs.

$ sudo gitlab-ctl reconfigure
need to configure the domain name in the configuration file so you can access GitLab. Open the file.

$ sudo vi  /etc/gitlab/gitlab.rb

In this file edit the 'external_url' and give the server domain. Save the file and then open the newly created GitLab site from a web browser.
Now open browser and type "Local IP of Server (200.0.0.30)"

By default it creates 'root' as the system admin and uses '5iveL!fe' as the password. Log into the GitLab site and then change the password.
From GUI create additional user(gitadmin) and Project/Repo named as TesT add a file and add some text and commit
Now git Local Git Server is Ready to work

Do some Testing


From Client  clone remote repo,create new branch  and make changes and pull to new branch
=====================================================================================

Log in as any user

$ git clone http://200.0.0.30/gitadmin/TestT.git

$ cd TestT
$ git status
$ ls -la


$ git config --list
$ git config --global user.name "tester"
$ git config --global user.email "tester@test.com"
$ git config --list


$ git checkout -b pro1
$ mkdir wall
$ mkdir wall
$ cp /home/ubuntu/Downloads/FireFox/4*.jpg wall/
$ ls wall/
$ cp /home/ubuntu/Downloads/FireFox/Git-VCS.pdf .

$ git status

$ git add .
$ git commit -m "Addes Files from 200.0.0.10"
$ git status

$ git remote -v

$ git push origin pro1

